columns.name: engine
columns.description: The name of the database engine.

columns.name: engine_version
columns.description: The version number of the database engine.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The ARN of the custom engine version.

columns.name: status
columns.description: The status of the DB engine version, either available or deprecated.

columns.name: create_time
columns.description: The creation time of the DB engine version.

columns.name: custom_db_engine_version_manifest
columns.description: JSON string that lists the installation files and parameters that RDS Custom uses to create a custom engine version (CEV).

columns.name: list_supported_character_sets
columns.description: A value that indicates whether to list the supported character sets for each engine version.

columns.name: db_engine_description
columns.description: The description of the database engine.

columns.name: db_engine_media_type
columns.description: A value that indicates the source media provider of the AMI based on the usage operation. Applicable for RDS Custom for SQL Server.

columns.name: db_engine_version_description
columns.description: The description of the database engine version.

columns.name: db_parameter_group_family
columns.description: The name of the DB parameter group family for the database engine.

columns.name: database_installation_files_s3_bucket_name
columns.description: The name of the Amazon S3 bucket that contains your database installation files.

columns.name: database_installation_files_s3_prefix
columns.description: The Amazon S3 directory that contains the database installation files. If not specified, then no prefix is assumed.

columns.name: kms_key_id
columns.description: The Amazon Web Services KMS key identifier for an encrypted CEV. This parameter is required for RDS Custom, but optional for Amazon RDS.

columns.name: major_engine_version
columns.description: The major engine version of the CEV.

columns.name: supports_babelfish
columns.description: A value that indicates whether the engine version supports Babelfish for Aurora PostgreSQL.

columns.name: supports_certificate_rotation_without_restart
columns.description: A value that indicates whether the engine version supports rotating the server certificate without rebooting the DB instance.

columns.name: supports_global_databases
columns.description: A value that indicates whether you can use Aurora global databases with a specific DB engine version.

columns.name: supports_log_exports_to_cloudwatch_logs
columns.description: A value that indicates whether the engine version supports exporting the log types specified by ExportableLogTypes to CloudWatch Logs.

columns.name: supports_parallel_query
columns.description: A value that indicates whether you can use Aurora parallel query with a specific DB engine version.

columns.name: supports_read_replica
columns.description: Indicates whether the database engine version supports read replicas.

columns.name: exportable_log_types
columns.description: The types of logs that the database engine has available for export to CloudWatch Logs.

columns.name: image
columns.description: The EC2 image.

columns.name: supported_feature_names
columns.description: A list of features supported by the DB engine.

columns.name: supported_nchar_character_sets
columns.description: A list of the character sets supported by the Oracle DB engine for the NcharCharacterSetName parameter of the CreateDBInstance operation.

columns.name: supported_timezones
columns.description: A list of the time zones supported by this engine for the Timezone parameter of the CreateDBInstance action.

columns.name: valid_upgrade_target
columns.description: A list of engine versions that this database engine version can be upgraded to.

columns.name: tag_list
columns.description: A list of tags.
